Related: employ, work

Labor costs can be safely minimized when object consumers are source controllers.

"'Whoever gives his labor for money sells himself and puts himself in the rank of slaves.'" -- Cicero


The following quote seems to say that automation would cause property loss.

"'Man can live and satisfy his wants only by ceaseless labor; by the ceaseless application of his faculties to natural resources. This process is the origin of property.'" -- "The Law" by Frederic Bastiat

